snippet.textDisplay: So a brief little thing. Dreads were first know to come from India. One of their gods (diety Shiva) are pictured to have dreads. It was also common in egypt as well (though the mummies in Egypt have another theory that they could have originated there aswell) In the bible Samson has magical dreadlocks and it's been known for other people in religious standings to have dreadlocks. Vikings were not found common to have dreads, but some did. So did Germanic tribes. Roman account have claimed that the celts wore their hair "like snakes".  Ethiopian orthodox tewahedo church. The nazarites of Judaism, the sadhus of Hinduism and the dervishes of islam, etc. This is just a brief history of dreads that many races have worn it. If you feel like one race should only wear that, than that's your opinion. If you feel like others should wear it, then that's you. I'm just here to give history about this so take these facts as you wish and use them as you please

snippet.textDisplay: Maybe, and this is just a theory of mine, LOCS not dreads AREN’T for white hair yah know. Y’all’s hair don’t benefit from any protective styles, y’all’s hair shades more so having it loced up for that long isn’t good. And it’s definitely cultural appropriation no matter how you spin it. You might think that “OMG locs are so cute, box braids are so cute ...” so on and so forth but stop getting them and using crazy excuses for having locs. If you don’t care about the culture you’re appropriating then at least care about your own hair.
